Class Description
ArgumentsParser
Parser for command line arguments.
Bio
Comprises static methods that implement algorithms to solve specifically bioinformatics problems.
CL
This class comprises static methods used for calling command line commands.
FastaEntry
Represents the entry from a `.fasta` file.
GeneFeature
Represents and stores information about a gene feature parsed from a `.gff` file.
InputPreprocessor
Comprises static methods to generate sets of ReferenceAnalysisEntry and SampleAnalysisEntry instances.
IO
This class comprises static methods used for reading and writing files.
Logging
This class comprises static methods used for status logging.
Musial
Main class of MUSIAL (MUlti Sample varIant AnaLysis), a tool to calculate SNV, gene, and whole genome alignments, together with other relevant statistics based on vcf files.
MusialCLAException
Command line argument exception of MUSIAL.
MusialDuplicationException
Duplication exception of MUSIAL.
MusialFaultyDataException
Faulty data exception of MUSIAL.
MusialIOException
IO exception of MUSIAL.
OutputWriter
Comprises a static method to generate all output files.
ReferenceAnalysisEntry
Internal representation of a reference sequence location that is subject to analysis.
SampleAnalyser
Comprises static methods to analyze samples.
SampleAnalyserRunnable
Implementation of the Runnable interface to analyze a sample.
SampleAnalysisEntry
Internal representation of a sample that is subject to analysis.
SamplePreprocessorRunnable
Implementation of the Runnable interface to preprocess a sample input.
SnpEffAnnotator
Runs local installation of SnpEff via command line.
SnpEffAnnotatorRunnable
Implementation of the Runnable interface to run SnpEff.
Validation
This class comprises static methods used for validating input data.
VariablePosition
Represents and stores information about a single genomic position of one sample relative to a reference (genetic sequence).
VariablePositionsTable
Major data structure to store the results of Musial.
VariablePositionTableComparator
Implementation of the java.util.Comparator<java.lang.String> interface to sort String representations of genome positions that may contain "I" characters to represent insertions according to their integer value and number of contained "I"s.
